Counting the number of occurrences of a particular tag

tag_ids <- tags %>%
  count(Tag, name = "num_of_ques") %>%
  filter(num_of_ques >= 100)

tag_correlations <- tags %>%
  semi_join(tag_ids, by = "Tag") %>%
  pairwise_cor(item = Tag, feature = Id) %>%
  filter(correlation >= 0.25)

Creating a network plot

graph_from_data_frame(d = tag_correlations, vertices = tag_ids %>% semi_join(tag_correlations, by = c("Tag" = "item1"))) %>%
    ggraph(layout = "fr") +
    geom_edge_link(aes(alpha = correlation)) +
    geom_node_point() +
    geom_node_text(aes(color = num_of_ques, label = name, size = 4), repel = TRUE) +
    theme_void(base_size = 16) +
    labs (title = "Ecosystem of R tags in Stack Overflow questions", subtitles = "Correlations are based on groupings of tags in stack overflow questions")
